and more stars

498
00:30:48,883 --> 00:30:52,000
One can see more and more stars
when going to the center 

499
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:53,698
Even more at
longer wavelengths.

500
00:30:53,698 --> 00:30:57,945
In this image
almost all the stars

501
00:30:57,945 --> 00:30:58,892
can be seen through the dust.

502
00:30:58,892 --> 00:31:03,343
This is a cloud of dust
in the Milky Way -

503
00:31:03,343 --> 00:31:09,040
Barnard 68 that can be
delimited in this way.

504
00:31:09,040 --> 00:31:13,085
This is an image in false colour

505
00:31:13,085 --> 00:31:17,840
with the visible light in the blue channel,

506
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:23,522
the near infrared in the green channel,

507
00:31:26,682 --> 00:31:30,646
and the infrared in the red channel.

508
00:31:31,167 --> 00:31:34,639
Looking at this image
one can at once see

509
00:31:34,639 --> 00:31:36,525
a large cloud of dust

510
00:31:36,525 --> 00:31:40,814
located along the line of sight
to the observer.

511
00:31:40,814 --> 00:31:44,513
Light constantly 
interacts with matter.

512
00:31:44,513 --> 00:31:47,473
Thanks to these interactions
the analysis of the light

513
00:31:47,473 --> 00:31:49,721
gives us valuable informations.

514
00:31:49,721 --> 00:31:53,004
The last two lectures showed that

515
00:31:53,004 --> 00:31:54,770
this analysis is quite delicate.

516
00:31:54,770 --> 00:31:58,081
All the physical processes at play must be taken 
into account simultaneously:

517
00:31:58,081 --> 00:32:02,666
continuous absorption or absorption lines,
continuous emission or emission lines,

518
00:32:02,666 --> 00:32:04,888
chromatic absorption, reflection,

519
00:32:04,888 --> 00:32:07,672
scattering which, in fact, is also
a chromatic phenomenon.

520
00:32:07,672 --> 00:32:11,556
Also, one needs to consider chromatic effects caused 
by the Doppler effect,

521
00:32:11,556 --> 00:32:14,466
rotation, thermal agitation 
of molecules 

522
00:32:14,466 --> 00:32:17,977
that sometimes broaden 
emission and absorption lines.

523
00:32:17,977 --> 00:32:21,082
All these phenomena 
play a role at some point,

524
00:32:21,082 --> 00:32:23,923
an important role in our
understanding of astronomical objects.
